By OKOSUN DENNIS
Troops of the 7 Division, Nigerian Army, have discovered high-calibre ammunition and weapons, including rockets, IEDs, kept by the Boko Haram insurgents in an IED factory.
The discovery was made at Kumshe, Borno, by the Strike Group Team B of the Division, on clearance operations of the remnants of the terrorists.
Spokesperson of the Nigerian Army, Colonel Sani Kukasheka Usman, added that the weapons would be destroyed as soon as preliminary analysis was concluded.

			
